snippet.textDisplay: I watched Lawnmower Man at the theater as a teenager and I while I knew only a little of cg at the time I remember thinking that this looks terrible compared to what I had seen in T2. A friend of at the time was dabbling in Lightwave at my Community College and was making better stuff than that, he (Craig Nisbet) did go on to work on Starship Troopers, Jimmy Newtron, and now works at Petroglyph, that said my opinion of Lawnmower Man was greatly jaded at the time. What a doo-doo movie.

snippet.textDisplay: My mom worked at a video store and I remember renting Lawnmower Man ( based on a story by Stephen King) the day it came out on video. I was lured in by Stephen Kings name on the box. I thought it was crappy animation and not what I thought CGI was at the time. But I knew it was a very low budget production company. It was still better than part II Jobs War, which the only thing I really remembered about that was they showed The PlayStation logo and PlayStation box before it was released. But back to the first lawnmower man, the movie was not even half as horrific as The Lawnmowers Man game for the Super Nintendo. And by the way I know this will be a big surprise but that movie had absolutely NOTHING to do with Kings story
